{
  "target": "distribution",
  "kind": "distribution",
  "source_test": "HEC.FDA.StatisticsTests/Distributions/LogPearsonIIITests.cs (LPIII_InverseCDF, BadValidation, GoodData_Returns_NoErrorState). InverseCDF cases use `new LogPearson3(mean, sd, skew)` (sampleSize defaults to 1) and assert `Math.Abs((output - result) / output) < .05` -> mode rel, tol 0.05, per the USGS-R SMWR oracle comments on each InlineData. BadValidation/GoodData cases call Validate() and assert HasErrors / ErrorLevel < Major; error_level values below were derived from LogPearson3.cs addRules() (see logpearson3.hpp comments): every failing BadValidation case fails at least one Fatal (0x20=32) rule and no Severe (successfullyLoggedData) rule ever fires from these constructor-only inputs, so composite error_level is always 32 (Fatal) for the bad cases and 0 (Unassigned) for the good cases.",
